# ecommerce-sql-analysis
End-to-end SQL analysis of a Brazilian ecommerce platform covering 99,441 orders across 25 months (Sept 2016 – Oct 2018). Built using PostgreSQL on Supabase, queries written in DBeaver.

## Dataset
7 interconnected tables: Customers, Orders, Order Items, 
Products, Sellers, Payments, Reviews.

| Table       | Rows    |
|-------------|---------|
| customers   | 99,441  |
| orders      | 99,441  |
| order_items | 112,650 |
| payments    | 103,886 |
| products    | 32,951  |
| sellers     | 3,095   |
| reviews     | 3,038   |

## Key Findings (Scroll through to view the SQL File with codes and interesting findings)

**Revenue & Geography**
- São Paulo generates R$5.77M — more than the next 4 states combined
- Top 3 states (SP, RJ, MG) account for the majority of platform revenue

**Growth Trend**
- Platform revenue grew ~20x in under 2 years (R$46K → R$1M+/month)
- November 2017 spike (+53.6% MoM) driven by Black Friday demand

**Delivery & Satisfaction**
- 78.93% of orders arrive 7+ days before the estimated date
- Late orders score avg 2.03/5 vs 4.31/5 for very early deliveries
- Delivery speed is the single biggest driver of customer satisfaction

**Sellers**
- 16 of top 20 sellers are based in São Paulo
- Two winning seller strategies: high volume (1,772 orders) vs 
  high ticket size (R$544 avg item price)

**Payments**
- Credit card dominates at 74% of transactions, avg 3.5 installments
- Boleto is a strong second — serves customers without credit access

